-- Indian shares retreat from record highs on profit-taking 
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Fri Apr 11, 2014 06:08AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, April 11 (Reuters) - Indian shares fell on Friday, retreating from record highs hit in the previous session as blue chips such as Reliance Industries <RELI.NS> retreated ahead of quarterly earnings and inflation data due next week.

Sentiment was also hit by a slide in global shares as steep falls in U.S. technology and biotechnology stocks spread to other sectors and regions. [MKTS/GLOB] Reliance Industries provisionally fell 1.8 percent, while Larsen & Toubro <LART.NS> ended lower 1.4 percent.